            <h1 class="text-center info-page-title">NASA</h1>
            <br />
            <p class="info-par">
                NASA, or the 'National Aeronautics and Space Administration' is a United States government agency that is responsible for science and technology related to air and space.
                NASA has countless contributions towards science and space travel. Astronauts in orbit are conducting scientific research. Satellites launched are helping scientests learn
                more about our own Earth.
                [<a href="https://www.nasa.gov/audience/forstudents/5-8/features/nasa-knows/what-is-nasa-58.html">REF</a>]<br />
            </p>
            <p class="info-par">
                Many of NASA's inventions have also seen commercial success and influenced many business markets. Some of NASA's greatest commercial inventions include
                smoke detectors, memory foam, cordless tools, shoe insoles, ear thermometers, scratch-resistant lenses and much more!
                [<a href="https://www.philips.com/c-w/malegrooming/philips-space/space/10-space-innovations-that-are-closer-than-you-think.html">REF</a>]
            </p>
            <br />
            NASA's offical website can be found here: <a href="https://www.nasa.gov/"> https://www.nasa.gov/ </a>

